1
00:00:10,375 --> 00:00:11,500
[NAGASUMI] Well, Sun...

2
00:00:11,583 --> 00:00:13,041
This is my house right
here, and it's your

3
00:00:13,125 --> 00:00:15,708
house as well now
that you're living with us.

4
00:00:16,541 --> 00:00:17,458
[SUN] Wow.

5
00:00:17,541 --> 00:00:18,791
It is a little small.

6
00:00:18,875 --> 00:00:20,125
But we all
still love it.

7
00:00:20,208 --> 00:00:22,666
[MAKI] Wow, it was
really cramped in there.

8
00:00:22,750 --> 00:00:25,125
You can't show your
face here, Maki!

9
00:00:25,208 --> 00:00:27,500
[MAKI] Are ya pickin a fight
with me ya fappy bastard?

10
00:00:27,583 --> 00:00:30,833
Well it's not gonna work out in
your favor, I'll have you know.

11
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:35,458
Miss! It's Nagasumi!
He's staring right at me again!

12
00:00:35,541 --> 00:00:39,083
Oh, Maki, you're so funny.
You're such a shy little person.

13
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,583
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Damn that stupid conch!

14
00:00:41,666 --> 00:00:43,041
Just thinking
about my new life

15
00:00:43,125 --> 00:00:44,291
living here with Sun has got my

16
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:47,375
heart racing a million
miles an hour.

17
00:00:47,458 --> 00:00:48,750
[NAGASUMI] But living
with an assassin who's

18
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:51,916
out to kill me might be
more than I can handle!

19
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,625
This is my house, after all!

20
00:00:53,708 --> 00:00:56,166
How am I supposed to
live my ordinary life like this?

21
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:59,416
What about my youth?
Which way is my tomorrow?

22
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,000
[SUN] I wonder if
this reaction of his is

23
00:01:01,083 --> 00:01:03,958
a symptom of some kinda illness.
I'd better be gentle with him.

24
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:09,958
[NARRATOR] Beneath
the gently rolling waves

25
00:01:10,041 --> 00:01:11,916
of the Seto Inland Sea.

26
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,583
Young Nagasumi's life is saved,
and forever changed.

27
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:19,291
But as with any debt,
this one too must be repaid.

28
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:21,125
So our story begins.

29
00:01:21,208 --> 00:01:25,375
Please humor them with a smile,
for young love is never easy.

30
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:33,125
♪

31
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:02,958
Dammit, Maki!

32
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,666
I told you not to show
your stupid face in public!

33
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,208
How exactly are we
supposed to explain

34
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:08,500
it if somebody sees you, huh?

35
00:03:08,583 --> 00:03:10,083
[MAKI] I'm sorry, Nagasumi.

36
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:12,416
Hey now, Nagasumi, don't
get so angry with Maki.

37
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,458
You're scaring her.

38
00:03:13,541 --> 00:03:15,625
See how upset she
is about it now?

39
00:03:15,708 --> 00:03:17,958
Your name is
Maki the Conch.

40
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:19,083
I couldn't believe
how incredibly

41
00:03:19,166 --> 00:03:21,250
cute you were the
first time I saw you!

42
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:23,333
[MAKI] You're making me blush!

43
00:03:23,416 --> 00:03:25,458
[NAGASUMI THINKS] Shit!
Maki's got them all fooled!

44
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:26,583
Don't you guys see!

45
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:29,083
She's an assassin
who's after my life!

46
00:03:29,166 --> 00:03:31,250
We're happy to have
you as well, Maki.

47
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:32,500
[MAKI] Thank you!]

48
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:33,833
[NAGASUMI] Is that all
you have to say, folks?

49
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:35,208
She's a teeny little girl
stuffed into a shell!

50
00:03:35,291 --> 00:03:36,916
Would you take anyone in?

51
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,958
Of course.

52
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:39,458
The house'll be
so bright and cheery

53
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:41,625
now that it's
all full of girls!

54
00:03:41,708 --> 00:03:43,250
Thank you for having us.

55
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:44,416
You are very welcome, Sun.

56
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,291
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Am I the only one who

57
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:47,166
thinks this is a little weird?

58
00:03:47,958 --> 00:03:49,833
Okay, Sun dear.

59
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:51,375
Starting today,
this room is yours.

60
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:53,083
It's all just for you!

61
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,250
[SUN] Wow!

62
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,375
[SUN] It looks a bit more like

63
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:58,750
a boy's room,
don't you think?

64
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,750
More like it's my
room, parents!

65
00:04:01,416 --> 00:04:03,583
[MAKI] It's the room of a
silly little child, sea louse.

66
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:04,208
It suits ya.

67
00:04:04,291 --> 00:04:05,500
You shut up, Maki!

68
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:07,833
Just surrender your
room quietly, Nagasumi.

69
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:08,875
[NAGASUMI] Oh?

70
00:04:08,958 --> 00:04:09,958
Where am I supposed
to sleep, huh?

71
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,916
Now, don't be
so worried about it.

72
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,708
You will not be
treated so badly.

73
00:04:13,791 --> 00:04:14,875
Yes, Nagasmui.

74
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,083
I am going to give you
your favorite room

75
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,833
in the whole house.

76
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:20,375
[DAD] The attic!

77
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:24,041
The attic's
for storage only!

78
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,125
It's perfect.

79
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:26,708
Besides, there
aren't any other rooms.

80
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:29,208
It's so exciting! You've
always loved the attic,

81
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:31,250
and now it'll be
your very own room!

82
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:32,791
I told you so
many times not to

83
00:04:32,875 --> 00:04:34,875
play in there, but I
couldn't keep you out.

84
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,416
You were just like
a little attic mouse.

85
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,583
[NAGASUMI] Dammit.

86
00:04:37,666 --> 00:04:38,750
Now they're comparing
me to an animal.]

87
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:39,458
Hooray!

88
00:04:39,541 --> 00:04:40,333
[NAGASUMI] Not really!

89
00:04:40,416 --> 00:04:42,791
[SUN] Mother, Father, excuse me.

90
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:45,083
I can't let ya
kick Nagasumi out

91
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,291
of his room and into the attic.

92
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:49,041
Really?

93
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:50,375
Of course.

94
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:52,375
Miss Sun and I can just
live in the drafty attic.

95
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:53,875
We'll be fine, really.

96
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,375
Please feel free to kick us

97
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:57,416
out of our room
and into the attic!

98
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,708
Oh! Miss Sun,
you poor thing!

99
00:04:59,791 --> 00:05:02,000
[NAGASUMI THINKS] She really
has a way of pissing me off.

100
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:03,250
You'd do that to a girl?

101
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,041
I'm disgusted
with you, Nagasumi!

102
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,000
Me too!

103
00:05:06,083 --> 00:05:07,416
Seriously, who raised
you, anyway?

104
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,916
[NAGASUMI]
You aren't funny, Mom.

105
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,250
[SUN] Ya see,
I just can't do it.

106
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:15,208
It's true Nagasumi and
I are still in junior high,

107
00:05:15,291 --> 00:05:18,958
and at this age, a room can
seem very important to a kid.

108
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:20,750
But I still can't force
my husband to be

109
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:24,250
in the attic for my personal
comfort or even just for a joke.

110
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:26,041
If I was to shame
my future husband

111
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:27,916
by doin' somethin' like that...

112
00:05:28,541 --> 00:05:31,833
It'd be a disgrace
to all Seto mermaids.

113
00:05:31,916 --> 00:05:33,375
Wow, Sun.

114
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:37,041
So thanks, but ya see, I'm
willing to live in the attic.

115
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:39,041
No. No, Sun,
don't worry about it.

116
00:05:39,125 --> 00:05:40,833
I'll take the attic.

117
00:05:40,916 --> 00:05:42,583
Oh, Nagasumi.

118
00:05:43,416 --> 00:05:44,916
[NAGASUMI THINKS] I wonder
how it is that Sun always

119
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,208
manages to make me want to

120
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:49,125
act more mature
than the kid that I am.

121
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:51,750
Livin' in the attic,
holed up in a cardboard

122
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:55,125
box is a perfect livin'
situation for ya, sea louse.

123
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:57,125
[NAGASUMI THINKS] And she
always manages to drag

124
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:59,916
me right back down
to my childhood.

125
00:06:05,708 --> 00:06:07,416
[NAGASUMI THINKS] This is
supposed to be my house.

126
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,791
No. No, I can't be
thinking like that anymore.

127
00:06:09,875 --> 00:06:11,666
My life here is bound to change.

128
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:14,166
That's what it means to live
with a new family, after all...

129
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:16,375
...accepting changes.

130
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:21,083
[NAGASUMI THINKS] Plus,
Sun must still be nervous

131
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:22,583
about living in a new place.

132
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:25,000
I need to hold
it together for her.

133
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:34,541
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Oh, wow.

134
00:06:34,625 --> 00:06:36,333
[Sun and Maki scream]

135
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:37,375
[Nagasumi cries out]

136
00:06:37,458 --> 00:06:39,500
[MAKI] Fappy sea louse!

137
00:06:39,583 --> 00:06:41,833
[MAKI] Why you.
Dirty little boy!

138
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,750
[MAKI] I can't
believe you'd lie in

139
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,750
wait to catch
Miss Sun in the bath!

140
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,000
I'm gonna send
ya straight to hell!

141
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:48,583
[DAD] What's all
that noise about?

142
00:06:48,666 --> 00:06:51,791
[things being broken]

143
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:54,166
My beautiful home, oh no!

144
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:56,000
[SUN] Oh my!
Mother! Father!

145
00:06:56,083 --> 00:06:59,250
[SUN] I'm so sorry.
I'm responsible for all this.

146
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,333
It was you, Sun?

147
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,500
Yes, I'm sorry.
I want you to have this.

148
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:05,916
Hopefully it can be
of some help to you.

149
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,333
[SUN] It's part of
my family's property,

150
00:07:07,416 --> 00:07:08,541
taken from a ship that sank

151
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:11,833
a long time ago in
the Seto Inland sea.

152
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:13,500
Gold.
Gold coins!

153
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,000
Oh my!

154
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,375
Feel free to break our bathroom
as many times as you want.

155
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:19,750
Ooh, a Jacuzzi!
Let's install a Jacuzzi!

156
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:22,041
But Sun dear,
why did you do it?

157
00:07:22,125 --> 00:07:23,291
Well, ya see...

158
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,958
Nagasumi was still in
the bath when I came in.

159
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:26,333
[MAKI] It was Nagasumi!

160
00:07:26,416 --> 00:07:28,041
[MAKI] Nagasumi waited
until Miss Sun and I

161
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:30,875
were about to take
a bath and then he, he--

162
00:07:31,875 --> 00:07:33,666
Forced his way in.

163
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,791
[DAD] You can take that,
mister Naughty-sumi!

164
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:41,083
[MOM] How horrible. I don't
know who he takes after.

165
00:07:41,166 --> 00:07:43,083
[MAKI] Nagasumi
is truly a beast.

166
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:45,250
[DAD] I could just die,
knowing I sired him.

167
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,583
[SUN] What?
No, wait. You're wrong.

168
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:49,791
[NAGASUMI] And yet,
I don't hear any apologies.

169
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:57,666
[NAGASUMI] Well, I guess it's
pretty well cleaned up now.

170
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:58,958
I really am so sorry to be

171
00:07:59,041 --> 00:08:00,958
takin' yer room
like this, Nagasumi.

172
00:08:01,041 --> 00:08:02,375
[NAGASUMI]
Hey, don't worry about it.

173
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:05,625
The attic won't be so bad
once I clean it up a bit.

174
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,958
But I've been
meaning to ask...

175
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:10,333
[NAGASUMI] What are
those things up there?

176
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:11,583
From Dad...

177
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:13,291
He insisted that I take
them along with me here.

178
00:08:13,375 --> 00:08:14,666
He insisted, huh?

179
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:15,916
Yep, he did.

180
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,916
Well, is there anything
else that you need now?

181
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,583
Huh.
Good question

182
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,291
[NAGASUMI] I know!
Let's go shopping.

183
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,500
I can show you
the neighborhood.

184
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:24,875
Yeah!
Sounds great.

185
00:08:24,958 --> 00:08:26,208
And we can bring Maki, too.

186
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:28,375
[NAGASUMI]
Oh, no! Maki is--

187
00:08:30,625 --> 00:08:33,166
[SUN] I guess Maki's
pretty tired out, huh?

188
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,625
She has been
goin' full steam 'an all.

189
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:37,125
[NAGASUMI] Yes, she has.

190
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:39,291
It would really be
a shame to wake her.

191
00:08:39,375 --> 00:08:41,708
Why don't the two of us
wander around by ourselves?

192
00:08:41,791 --> 00:08:42,916
Yeah, okay!

193
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,708
[NAGASUMI] Woo-hoo!
No Maki! Yes! Yes! Yes!

194
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:51,333
[SUN] Wow! That's the
third one so far!

195
00:08:51,416 --> 00:08:54,083
There are so many convenience
stores in your neighborhood!

196
00:08:54,166 --> 00:08:55,208
So I take it there aren't

197
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:56,541
too many around
your place, huh?

198
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:58,875
Yeah, our store
was really far away.

199
00:08:58,958 --> 00:08:59,958
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
Of course, you idiot.

200
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,833
Her house was at
the bottom of the sea.

201
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:04,375
[SUN] Only 100 yen,
it says! Only 100 yen!

202
00:09:04,458 --> 00:09:07,208
[SUN] I'll have some jakoten and
some beans with soy sauce.

203
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:09,000
[SUN] I'm not gonna lose
to some darn mole!

204
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:10,041
Take that mole!

205
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:11,083
[SUN] Oh wow!

206
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,916
Look, buses come
every few minutes.

207
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,625
And there are so many!

208
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,125
[SUN] This is a
real huge city, huh?

209
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,541
[NAGASUMI] Well, no, not really.

210
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:22,791
[NAGASUMI] But I guess that,

211
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,791
compared to your town,
it is kinda big, huh?

212
00:09:24,875 --> 00:09:27,208
It's a fun place
with so many stores!

213
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:29,416
I'm glad you like it.
This is a lot of fun!

214
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,791
[both laugh]

215
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:32,333
[NAGASUMI THINKS]
It's so peacefully normal

216
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:33,708
walking around with Sun.

217
00:09:33,791 --> 00:09:35,083
Just the two of us!

218
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:37,750
I wish this time without
Maki could last forever!

219
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:39,833
That would be perfect!

220
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:44,333
[MOM] Ahh.. She's out like
a light. How cute!

221
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,250
[MOM] She looks
like a little angel.

222
00:09:47,708 --> 00:09:49,041
[MAKI] I'll kill
you and tear off

223
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:51,791
your freakin' head, sea louse.

224
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:54,916
[MAKI] I'll see your guts
spilled all over the floor.

225
00:09:56,166 --> 00:09:57,791
[SUN] What's wrong?

226
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,875
A chill just ran down
my spine suddenly.

227
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:02,291
Are ya okay? Do we
need to head back home?

228
00:10:02,375 --> 00:10:03,708
Yeah, yeah, I think so.

229
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:04,833
[GIRL A] No!

230
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,750
[BOY A] What's all of this
stupid screaming about, huh?

231
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:08,833
Ow, let me go.

232
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:10,291
Come on. We're just
askin' if you two

233
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:12,083
wanna grab some tea with us.

234
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:13,958
[SUN] Hey, you there!

235
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,125
What're ya doin'?

236
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:16,916
[NAGASUMI] Wait, Sun!
Stop! Please stop!

237
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,666
There's a police
station nearby, okay?

238
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:21,125
Telling off guys like that
yourself is a bad idea.

239
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,291
But I'm a mermaid.
I can take 'em down easily.

240
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:26,666
If anybody sees you
then you're dead meat!

241
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,166
You can't use
